description:
In this episode, we query Martin Luther's protest from 500 years ago, as it is still debated at length. Is it still valid? Are the reasons for it still relevant? Is it now outdated, or have people today simply forgotten the lessons of history? Many questions are still asked, but the issues that introduced the Reformation are indeed still relevant to the church today. 

To find out more information about Martin Luther read our extended article.
